commit.message:
Document metadata_directory arg + errors in runlib

Signed-off-by: Lukas Puehringer <lukas.puehringer@nyu.edu>

Add a flag to accept a target directory to put generated metadata in

Added an extra optional flag '--metadata-directory' to the 'in-toto run' and the
'in-toto record stop' arguments; updated related methods in 'in_toto_record.py',
'in_toto_run.py', and 'runlib.py'; and added one test to 'test_in_toto_record.py',
one test to 'test_in_toto_run.py', and nine tests to 'test_runlib.py". If this flag
is passed, the resulting link metadata file will be dumped to the target directory.
Otherwise, the default destination is the current working directory.

Signed-off-by: SolidifiedRay <yc3346@nyu.edu>

Add windows dev mode hint to symlink tests

Added an extra method '_raise_win_dev_mode_error' to the 'Test_ApplyExcl
udePatterns' class in test_runlib.py, and updated 3 other methods to inc
lude it . It checks if the user is on a Windows platform. If so, they ar
e informed that Developer mode is required to work with symlinks on Wind
ows, and asked if it is enabled.

commit.message:
Enable API + metadata model class sphinx auto-docs

+ some minor updates on the docs landing page, like pointers to
other in-toto resources.

Signed-off-by: Lukas Puehringer <lukas.puehringer@nyu.edu>

Fix minor syntax issues in installation docs

Fix issues that occurred after swithing to sphinx-rtd-theme.

Signed-off-by: Lukas Puehringer <lukas.puehringer@nyu.edu>

Update misc sphinx doc config

- Switch from alabaster to sphinx_rtd_theme
- Add napoleon sphinx extension to parse Google-style docstrings
- Add todo sphinx extension (for utils docs)
- Comment out currently unused html_static_path that triggered a
  warning

Signed-off-by: Lukas Puehringer <lukas.puehringer@nyu.edu>

Move layout creation sample code to sphinx docs

Signed-off-by: Lukas Puehringer <lukas.puehringer@nyu.edu>

Move settings docs from README.md to sphinx docs

+ revise and update

Signed-off-by: Lukas Puehringer <lukas.puehringer@nyu.edu>

Revise + consolidate docstring format and contents

Revise/shorten/consolidate/update main API function-, class- and
method- docstrings:

 - verifylib.in_toto_verify
 - runlib.in_toto_run
 - runlib.in_toto_record_start
 - runlib.in_toto_record_stop
 - models.metadata.Metablock
 - models.link.Link
 - models.layout.Layout
 - models.layout.Step
 - models.layout.Inspection
 - models.common.Signable (only parts relevant for read the docs)
 - models.common.ValidationMixin (only relevant parts)

Changes custom Secure Systems Lab docstring format to Google
format, which is machine- (sphinx) and human-readable.
(Choosing Google over NumPy because it requires less vertical
space, see
https://sphinxcontrib-napoleon.readthedocs.io/en/latest/#google-vs-numpy)

Signed-off-by: Lukas Puehringer <lukas.puehringer@nyu.edu>
